      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOBY KEEPING (4) is a sprinter who excels over the short dashes. Was in the money last time (30.98) over 530m at Angle Park in a Grade 5 but is better suited by this sharper distance. Goes very well at the journey winning one races. Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Sure to be about the mark. YVONNE'S PICK (1) missed the frame latest when seventh at Murray Bridge (17.65) but scored five back at this track (16.87). Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Cannot be underestimated. SHINY PISTOL (6) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fifth (17.30) at this track. Solid record here winning six races. Has good speed so he should be prominent despite the draw. Has the ability to give this a shake.",
